arm_group.description:
abrupt withdrawal of overuse symptomatic drugs, with possibility to use indomethacin suppository 50-100 mg or an oral triptan, on maximum 3 days/10 days, only in case of very severe headache- and to use metoclopramide i.m. injection in case of vomiting;
oral administration of a bridge therapy to reduce the withdrawal symptoms and rebound headache (prednisone 25 mg , 2 tablets after breakfast for 5 days, one tablet for 3 days, half tablet for 2 days ; bromazepam 1.5 mg, 1 tablet after breakfast, lunch and dinner for every day; pantoprazole 40 mg, 1 tablet after dinner every day);
mindfulness practice daily with standard sessions by smartphone 6 minutes per day.
